<h1><span id="Caro-Kann_Defence:_Exchange_Variation">Caro-Kann Defence: Exchange Variation</span></h1>
<p>White exchanges on d5, and black almost always responds with cxd5. This forms opposite-wing majorities. This usually will lead into a Panov-Botvinnik Attack, although independent lines can arise after 4.Bd3.
